# ZON Modular Syntax

## Top-Level Order

`name`, `version`, `targets`, `defaults`, `dependencies`, `tests`, `profiles`. Use `//` for section headers.

## Targets (Map Format)

Use `.@"name" = .{ ... }` for named targets.

```zon
.targets = .{
    .@"{{PROJECT_NAME}}" = .{
        .type = .executable,
        .sources = .{"src/**/*.cpp"},
        .include_dirs = .{"include"},
        .flags = .{ .common = .{ "-Wall" }, .release = .{"-flto"} },
    },
},
```

## Nested Structs

One field per line. Inline short arrays: `.common = .{ "-Wall", "-Wextra" }`.

## Workspace

- `.members` or `.member_patterns` for packages
- `.shared` for common settings
- `.workspace_dependencies` for shared deps

## Templates

Placeholders: `{{PROJECT_NAME}}`, `{{AUTHOR_NAME}}`, `{{AUTHOR_EMAIL}}`
